India Sells 91-Day Bills at 8.44%, 364-Day Securities at 8.46%

-- B y   J e a n e t t e   R o d r i g u e s
-- 
2011-09-21T09:45:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/india-sells-91-day-bills-at-8-44-364-day-securities-at-8-46-.html
India â€™s borrowing costs for three
months and one year increased as it sold 100 billion rupees of
treasury bills at a weekly auction, the central bank said.  The government sold 70 billion rupees of 91-day bills at a
minimum price of 97.94 per 100 rupee face amount, or a maximum
yield of 8.4364 percent, compared with 8.3946 percent on Aug.
14, the Reserve Bank of India said in an e-mailed statement
today. It also auctioned 30 billion rupees of 364-day bills at a
cut-off price of 92.22 rupees, or a yield of 8.4595 percent,
compared with 8.3417 percent on Aug. 7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
